OL,3,CConstruction companies struggle to
OL,4,Ctake on apprentices after minimum wage
OL,5,Crise
OL,7,FA construction company in Jersey says
OL,8,Fthey cannot afford to take on new
OL,9,Fapprentices after the introduction of
OL,10,Fthe minimum wage.
OL,12,FBrady & Gallagher has trained hundreds
OL,13,Fof apprentices over the last 50 years,
OL,14,Fbut since Jersey's government scrapped
OL,15,Ftrainee rates of pay, the company says
OL,16,Fit can no longer afford to take staff
OL,17,Fon.
OL,19,FIt comes as the Jersey Construction
OL,20,FCouncil warned that the company is not
OL,21,Fthe only one on the island struggling.
