OL,7,FThe Minister for Social Security,
OL,8,FDeputy Lyndsay Feltham, told ITV News:
OL,9,F"Government is supporting businesses
OL,10,Fwith a #20 million package of measures
OL,11,Fdesigned to improve skills, promote
OL,12,Fproductivity, and protect
OL,13,Fcompetitiveness as part of its
OL,14,Fpriority to implement the living wage.
OL,16,F"If approved by the States Assembly as
OL,17,Fpart of this week's Budget debate,
OL,18,Fthis package includes a #2 million
OL,19,Fskills grant to help invest in
OL,20,Femployee apprentice and skills
OL,21,Ftraining.
